<p>There are a series of massive, interconnected problems in the world of academic publishing – predatory journals; unpaid and unrewarded labour; reviewers that are either conflicted in, or unsuited to, their roles; perverse incentives in article selection; and even research that should be published and is actively suppressed.</p>
